

The numbers are placed on a hexagonal “snail’’ (counter‑clockwise) :

```
1 : (0,0)
→ 2 : (1,0)      → 3 : (0,1)      → 4 : (‑1,1)
→ 5 : (‑1,0)    → 6 : (0,‑1)      → 7 : (1,‑1)
```

After the first ring the walk continues as  

```
E 1 step, NE 1 step,
NW n steps, W n steps, SW n steps, SE n steps,
E n steps               (n ≥ 2)
```

Thus for number \(N>1\)

* let \(n\) be the ring, i.e. the smallest integer with  
  \(3n(n-1)+2\le N\le 3n(n+1)+1\);
* put \(p=N-\bigl(3n(n-1)+2\bigr)\) (the position in the ring, \(0\le p\le6n-1\));
* the coordinates \((q,r)\) are obtained from the segment in which \(p\) lies:

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{segment}&(q,r) \\
\hline
\text{start}&(n,\;-(n-1))\\[2pt]
\text{NE }(1\le p\le n-1)&(n,\;-(n-1)+p)\\[2pt]
\text{NW }(n\le p\le2n-1)&(2n-p-1,\;p-n+1)\\[2pt]
\text{W }(2n\le p\le3n-1)&(-(p-2n+1),\;n)\\[2pt]
\text{SW }(3n\le p\le4n-1)&(-n,\;4n-p-1)\\[2pt]
\text{SE }(4n\le p\le5n-1)&(-n+p-4n+1,\;-(p-4n+1))\\[2pt]
\text{E }(5n\le p\le6n-1)&(p-5n+1,\;-n)
\end{array}
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026

\[
3n(n-1)+2\le2026\le3n(n+1)+1\Longrightarrow n=26
\]

\[
p =2026-\bigl(3\cdot26\cdot25+2\bigr)=2026-1952=74 .
\]

Since \(2n=52\le p\le3n-1=77\), 2026 lies on the **West side** of ring 26:

\[
(q,r)=\bigl(-(p-2n+1),\;n\bigr)=(-23,26).
\]

---

### 2.  The six neighbours

Using the axial directions  

\[
(1,0),\;(0,1),\;(-1,1),\;(-1,0),\;(0,-1),\;(1,-1)
\]

the neighbour coordinates are  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{direction}&(q',r')\\\hline
\text{E}&(-22,26)\\
\text{NE}&(-23,27)\\
\text{NW}&(-24,27)\\
\text{W}&(-24,26)\\
\text{SW}&(-23,25)\\
\text{SE}&(-22,25)
\end{array}
\]

---

### 3.  Convert each neighbour back to a number

*Ring 26 (same as 2026) – West side*  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-22,26)&\Rightarrow p=73\Rightarrow N=1952+73=2025,\\
(-24,26)&\Rightarrow p=75\Rightarrow N=1952+75=2027.
\end{aligned}
\]

*Ring 27 – West side*  

For ring 27, \(f(27)=3\cdot27\cdot26+2=2108\).

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-23,27)&\Rightarrow p=76\Rightarrow N=2108+76=2184,\\
(-24,27)&\Rightarrow p=77\Rightarrow N=2108+77=2185.
\end{aligned}
\]

*Ring 25 – West side*  

For ring 25, \(f(25)=3\cdot25\cdot24+2=1802\).

\[
\begin{aligned}
(-23,25)&\Rightarrow p=72\Rightarrow N=1802+72=1874,\\
(-22,25)&\Rightarrow p=71\Rightarrow N=1802+71=1873.
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &= 2025+2027+2184+2185+1873+1874 \\
  &= (2025+2027) + (2184+2185) + (1873+1874)\\
  &= 4052 + 4369 + 3747\\
  &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
